The paper deals with the problem of maximizing a submodular set function, which is a fundamental problem in computer science and falls under the category of algorithms and data structures (cs.DS). The paper also discusses approximation algorithms, which are commonly studied in the fields of artificial intelligence (cs.AI) and machine learning (cs.LG). The use of statistics and prior distributions in the algorithms suggests that the paper may also fall under the category of computational complexity (cs.CC). Finally, the paper discusses a case study using data from an online platform, which suggests that it may also belong to the category of game theory (cs.GT).
